docs.abstract: Swedish citizen Peter Dahlin recounts being jailed and interrogated for 23 days by China's Ministry of State Security, spy and counterespionage agency; Dahlin and his Chinese Urgent Action Working Group are one of many foreign nonprofit organizations being targeted by Pres Xi Jinping for undermining Communist party rule; Dahlin--who maintains his group was working to develop independent judiciary--was accused of funding criminal activities harmful to national security and deported from China in January.
